<Tab title="With prefix callback">

Computes an exclusive block-wide prefix scan using the specified binary \`scan_op\` functor. Each thread contributes one input element. The call-back functor \`block_prefix_callback_op\` is invoked by the first warp in the block, and the value returned by *lane*<sub>0</sub> in that warp is used as the "seed" value that logically prefixes the thread block's scan inputs.

