## Inner classes

### TempStorage

<CodeBlock links={{"WarpReduce": "/library/api/cub::WarpReduce"}}>
\`\`\`cpp showLineNumbers={false}
struct cub::WarpReduce::TempStorage
\`\`\`
</CodeBlock>

The operations exposed by [WarpReduce](/library/api/cub::WarpReduce) require a temporary memory allocation of this nested type for thread communication. This opaque storage can be allocated directly using the \`__shared__\` keyword. Alternatively, it can be aliased to externally allocated memory (shared or global) or \`union\`'d with other storage allocation types to facilitate memory reuse.

**Inherits from:** \`Uninitialized< _TempStorage >\` (public)
"
`;
